            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20depression%2C%20David%20had%20obviously%20reached%20a%20point%20of%20such%20despair%20that%20he%20was%20sure%20his%20troubles%20numbered%20more%20than%20the%20hairs%20of%20his%20head.%20Paul%20was%20in%20a%20similar%20position%20in%20the%20battles%20he%20faced%20in%20Asia.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%22I%20think%20you%20ought%20to%20know%2C%20dear%20brothers%20and%20sisters%2C%20about%20the%20trouble%20we%20went%20through%20in%20the%20province%20of%20Asia.%20We%20were%20crushed%20and%20completely%20overwhelmed%2C%20and%20we%20thought%20we%20would%20never%20live%20through%20it%22%20(2%20Corinthians%201%3A8).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EEven%20in%20that%20kind%20of%20pressure%2C%20Paul%20found%20a%20secret%20that%20sustained%20him.%20He%20discovered%20God%20as%20the%20%22source%20of%20every%20mercy%20and%20the%20God%20who%20comforts%20us%22%20(2%20Corinthians%201%3A3).%20When%20God%20comforts%20us%20and%20shows%20us%20His%20mercy%2C%20it%20has%20a%20double%20effect%3A%20we%20learn%20to%20rely%20more%20on%20Him%2C%20and%20others%20learn%20from%20our%20deliverance.%20We%20can%20never%20totally%20identify%20with%20others%20until%20we%20have%20walked%20their%20paths%2C%20and%20God%20will%20use%20our%20troubles%20to%20become%20a%20testimony%20to%20others%20in%20need.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ELift%20up%20your%20head%20and%20let%20the%20God%20of%20all%20comfort%20minister%20to%20you%20right%20now.%20Then%20%22many%20will%20give%20thanks%22%20(2%20Corinthians%201%3A11)%20to%20God%20on%20your%20behalf%2C%20and%20God%20will%20be%20glorified%20in%20it%20all.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
